1.title: To Elle and Back
1.plot: Ben is still desperately searching for the mysterious Elle. Danny and Riley hunt for a good doctor to help with the pregnancy and Bonnie desperately wants to be involved.

2.title: Pro and Con
2.plot: Ben suspects that Tucker went on a date with a hooker, so he and Danny set out to prove it.

3.title: Ben Rides a Unicorn
3.plot: Now that Danny has moved in with Riley, Emma gets her own room and Ben realizes that he can finally have sex in his room again.

4.title: A Mother of a Day
4.plot: Tucker learns the Mother's Day special he produced was nominated for a New York Entertainment Award. Tucker's mom surprises him by showing up to be his plus one to the ceremony, which throws a wrench in Tucker's plans to have Bonnie pose as his mom. Riley begins to show in her pregnancy and worries if this will hold her back from being promoted.

5.title: When Elle Freezes Over
5.plot: Sam comes back into the picture wanting to give her and Ben's relationship another chance, but Ben hesitates on whether or not that's a good idea as he's still searching for the mysterious Elle. Danny and Tucker volunteer for a charity ice skating show featuring Emma's favorite princess, while Riley practices parenting.

6.title: The Third Wheeler
6.plot: Danny is being overprotective of pregnant Riley, so Ben surprises Riley with a day off and a hike in the woods.

7.title: The Sonny-Moon
7.plot: Ben gets jealous when he learns that Bonnie is sending Danny on a cruise to celebrate becoming a dad, so he and Danny hold a Wheeler War to see who deserves the trip more.

8.title: You Cruise, You Lose
8.plot: Danny and Riley go on their babymoon cruise, but Bonnie decides to tag along after Danny reveals that he hopes he and Riley will elope.

9.title: The Rebound
9.plot: Riley wants to move because of apartment size so Danny tries to make it better with disastrous results. Tucker wants his old girlfriend Sondra back who's newly single but sends Ben in to be her rebound guy.

10.title: What's in the Box?!
10.plot: Danny and Ben are eager to find out the sex of the baby, even though Riley would prefer it to be a surprise.

11.title: Daddy's Girl
11.plot: Ben begins to feel like an insufficient parent when Emma's upcoming Mother-Daughter Talent Show leads Emma to ask questions about why she doesn't have a mother.

1.title: Pilot
1.plot: Twenty-something Ben decides to give parenting a shot.

2.title: I Told You So
2.plot: Ben and the boys come up with a fool-proof babysitting schedule.

3.title: The Nurse and the Curse
3.plot: Ben hits it off with Emma's nurse.

4.title: Guys, Interrupted
4.plot: Bonnie's presence at the boys' apartment disrupts their routine.

5.title: Married to the Job
5.plot: A potential new boss assumes Ben and Riley are married.

6.title: Take Her Out of the Ballgame
6.plot: Riley is voted team captain of Ben's softball team.

7.title: May the Best Friend Win
7.plot: Ben and Tucker are at odds when they date the same girl.

8.title: The Daddy Whisperer
8.plot: Ben has a one-on-one to clean up his act at an elite Mommy and Me class.

9.title: A Wheeler Family Christmas Outing
9.plot: Ben tries to bring everyone together for Emma's first Christmas photo.

10.title: Something Borrowed, Something Ben
10.plot: Riley is in Maid of Honor mode as she counts down to Katie's wedding.

1.title: I'm Not That Guy
1.plot: Riley is convinced that Ben is "that guy."

2.title: There's Something Fitchy Going On
2.plot: Ben thinks that Fitch is married and wants to warn Riley.

3.title: The Wheeler and the Dealer
3.plot: Ben hears about an energy drink endorsement opportunity for Danny.

4.title: New Bonnie vs. Old Ben
4.plot: Bonnie is moving into the city, right across the hall from the boys.

5.title: The Slump
5.plot: Ben has his eye on Tucker's co-worker Jenna.

6.title: Ben's Big Gay-Care Adventure
6.plot: Ben tries to find a daycare for Emma.

7.title: On the Lamb-y
7.plot: When Emma's stuffed animal goes missing, Ben is convinced someone stole it.

8.title: Never Ben in Love
8.plot: Riley plans to end her relationship with Fitch, but discovers that he died.

9.title: All's Flair in Love and War
9.plot: Tucker and his ex-girlfriend, Vanessa, start up their relationship again.

10.title: Test Anxiety
10.plot: Riley questions her future after taking the bar exam.

11.title: Whatever Lola Wants
11.plot: Ben's girlfriend's dog is stolen while under his care.

12.title: The Christening
12.plot: Everyone gets together for Emma's christening - including Ben's dad.

13.title: All Riled Up
13.plot: Ben starts to wonder if he and Riley would make a good couple.

14.title: The Playdate's the Thing/The Emma Dilemma
14.plot: Ben and Tucker set up a rival playgroup.

15.title: Surprise!
15.plot: Ben throws Riley a birthday party. Bonnie and Tucker track down Emma's mom.

16.title: Emma's First Christmas
16.plot: Ben is on a mission to find the most popular toy for Emma's first Christmas, but all the stores are sold out.

1.title: The Naked Truth
1.plot: Ben and Riley try to jumpstart their relationship but Emma's mom, Angela, gets in the way. Tucker tries to help Danny get over his failed relationships.

2.title: The Lying Game
2.plot: Riley wonders if Ben should give family life with Angela a shot.

3.title: Lights! Camera! No Action!
3.plot: Tucker scores Danny an interview on the Mary Hart Show.

4.title: Bonnie's Unreal Estate
4.plot: Bonnie's new boss gives her an impossible apartment listing.

5.title: Life's a Beach
5.plot: The guys start a campaign to be on their building's Resident Board so they can keep their rooftop beach. Riley and Bonnie go on a double date.

6.title: Romancing the Phone
6.plot: Ben and Tucker swap names while pursuing a woman. Elsewhere, Riley runs into a former rival and enlists Danny in a revenge scheme; and Bonnie gets Tucker to assist her in creating a slogan for her new business.

7.title: The Bet
7.plot: Ben tries to score a second date with Heather in order to win a wager with Riley. Elsewhere, Bonnie asks Danny to end her relationship with Brad for her, and then she becomes interested in Brad's dad; and Tucker uses Emma to improve his dating life.

8.title: A Knight to Remember
8.plot: Tucker pretends to be a lawyer in order to please his dad, and Ben helps with the charade. Meanwhile, Riley develops a crush on a British guy, but Bonnie mistakenly thinks she's fallen for Danny; and the gang's trip to a Renaissance faire goes badly.

9.title: Go Brit or Go Home
9.plot: Phillip may lose his visa thanks to Ben. Meanwhile, Danny dates a sports reporter; and Tucker adopts a phony British accent to impress women.

10.title: An Affair Not to Remember
10.plot: Tucker's new girlfriend used to date Ben but doesn't seem to remember. Riley is invited to a spa day with her boss.

11.title: The Wingmom
11.plot: Bonnie sets Ben up on a date with an energetic gal who's similar to herself. Elsewhere, Danny gets his dad's cherished car out of storage, but problems arise when Riley and Tucker take it for a spin.

12.title: Send in the Clowns
12.plot: Ben throws a bash for Emma's first birthday and puts Tucker in charge of entertainment. Meanwhile, Ben encounters an ex-girlfriend who's hiding a big secret; and Danny uncovers shocking news about Riley's family.

13.title: Play It Again, Bonnie
13.plot: Riley starts a new romance. Meanwhile, Bonnie wants to rekindle things with Brad, so she asks for Tucker's assistance.

14.title: Livin' on a Prom
14.plot: Ben takes Bonnie to a Bon Jovi concert to thank her for all she does, but the tickets Tucker gets him are counterfeit. Elsewhere, Danny's former vice principal inappropriately flirts with him when he and Riley chaperone a prom at their old high school.

15.title: From Here to Paternity
15.plot: Riley tries to figure out who her biological father is and comes up with two candidates. Elsewhere, Tucker blames his dad for his parents' impending divorce, so Bonnie attempts to help by getting Tucker's father to be less rigid.

16.title: Curious Georgie
16.plot: Philip's sister is less than impressed with Riley; Bonnie's actions threaten Danny's career.

17.title: Flirty Dancing
17.plot: Ben, Danny, and Riley take stock of their lives when they review their fifth-grade time capsules.

18.title: Baby Steps
18.plot: Ben wants to see Emma walk and tries bribing her with food, but it doesn't work. Instead, she toddles after he leaves for work, so the gang devise a scheme for him not to miss out on this milestone. Meanwhile, everyone reflects on Emma's infancy.

19.title: Foos It or Lose It
19.plot: Ben and Tucker pose as fraternity pledges after Bonnie sells their money-stuffed foosball table.

20.title: All Aboard the Love Train
20.plot: Ben hopes to rekindle his romance with Riley when he joins her on a train trip to Florida.

21.title: You Can't Go Home Again
21.plot: Ben and Riley learn the truth about Danny's feelings for Riley; Danny considers moving to Paris.

1.title: Strip or Treat
1.plot: Riley decides to pull a prank on everyone after all the jokes they've played on her over the years.

2.title: It's a Wonderful Emma
2.plot: Ben gets in a bad mood as Christmas approaches, so he makes a wish that the holiday never existed. His wish is granted, but he's unprepared for the consequences: Emma's existence is erased and everyone's lives are on different courses.

3.title: She Loves Me, She Loves Me Note
3.plot: Ben starts to think that Riley might be in love with Danny, so he comes up with a plan to find out the truth.

4.title: I See Crazy People
4.plot: While trying to convince Riley that they are soulmates, Ben realizes he knows none of her favorite things. Bonnie resists Tucker's efforts to get her to move out and Danny continues to pretend to be in Paris.

5.title: Mugging for the Camera
5.plot: Ben and Riley are attacked by a mugger and Danny saves the day, but needs to stay anonymous. Tucker thinks the story is perfect to save his job at Mary Hart's show.

6.title: Over My Dead Bonnie
6.plot: Riley is estatic when Danny is offered a bit part on General Hospital, her favorite show. In continuing to scheme to get Bonnie's apartment back, Tucker pretends to hold a funeral and Bonnie misrepresents Ben as a gay man.

7.title: The Mother of All Dates
7.plot: Ben and Danny compete to see who can pair Bonnie up with the perfect date.

8.title: House of Cards
8.plot: Riley abuses her corporate card and tries to enlist Ben and Danny's help to explain the charges.

9.title: An Officer and a Gentle Ben
9.plot: Riley denies having feelings for Danny but she continually interrupts his date with her co-worker. Ben and Tucker dress up as sailors during Fleet Week to meet girls while Bonnie tries to find a nice way to end a relationship.

10.title: Happy Birthday Two You
10.plot: While planning Bonnie's party, Ben accidentally lets Danny know he was lied to about his actual birth date. Riley and Tucker try to hide the fact that Emma had an accident while they were watching her.

11.title: You Give Real Estate a Bad Name
11.plot: Bonnie must compete with Brad to win the opportunity to sell Bon Jovi's amazing apartment.

12.title: A Love/Fate Relationship
12.plot: Riley finally confesses her feelings for Danny just as he is about to leave for a weekend with Robyn. Ben and Bonnie come up with a fake secret admirer to help Tucker out of his doldrums. It gets complicated when she is told Tucker has a terminal illness.

13.title: Home Is Where the Wheeler Is
13.plot: After making a mess of her confession to Danny, Riley retreats to her parents' house to hide.

14.title: It Takes a Village Idiot
14.plot: Ben is accused of letting the others provide most of Emma's care so he announces he can do it all himself. Riley makes up a boyfriend while Danny and Bonnie take a class with temperamental chef Tommy Kwan.

15.title: One Night Stand Off
15.plot: Ben and Riley compete with each other playing a game in a bar - whoever makes out with a stranger first wins. Danny makes an investment.

16.title: Lowering the Bar
16.plot: Bonnie thinks Danny and Ben buying the bar is a bad idea and uses underhanded means to sabotage them. Riley takes Tucker's damage lawsuit to court but finds out too late the case is based on falsehoods.

17.title: Wheeler War
17.plot: Ben tries to corrupt Riley's kindhearted boyfriend; Bonnie attempts to join the boys' poker game.

18.title: Parental Guidance Suggested
18.plot: Ben has a health crisis and needs to choose a guardian for Emma. Bonnie's ex Brad returns but pretends to be his twin Thad to try and get Bonnie back.

19.title: Ring Around the Party
19.plot: Riley throws a party to meet Ross' friends; Danny tries to learn more about his new girlfriend.

20.title: Till Dress Do Us Part
20.plot: The gang fails to protect a possession of Bonnie's while reminiscing about their various entanglements.

21.title: What Happens in Vegas
21.plot: Bonnie enlists Riley to plan her bachelorette party, but when Bonnie learns of Brad's plans, she decides to crash.

22.title: It's a Nice Day for a Wheeler Wedding
22.plot: Bonnie's "frenemy" Charlotte helps Bonnie prepare for the wedding, but may have other plans up her sleeve.

1.title: Love and Carriage
1.plot: Riley faints after Danny asks her to marry him, and when she wakes up, has no memory of his proposal. Trying to move on from Riley, Ben immediately hits it off with new neighbor Zoey.

2.title: Reinventing the Wheeler
2.plot: Ben wants to get back into the dating scene but Riley decides she needs to "fix" him first so he will be a better boyfriend. Bonnie gets Danny high but has to think fast when the hockey team drug tests.

3.title: Ben-geance
3.plot: Ben seeks"Ben-Geance" on the girl who spurned him in high school, Bonnie decides marrying Brad might not have been a good idea and Danny can't stomach Riley's cooking, but doesn't have the heart to tell her.

4.title: The Tuck Stops Here
4.plot: A video of Mary Hart berating Tucker goes viral after Emma accidentally uploads it online. Bonnie is left alone after Brad leaves to volunteer overseas and tries to spend all her time with Danny, much to Riley's chagrin.

5.title: The Dating Game
5.plot: Ben begs Danny to find out if Sam is interested in dating him but she thinks Danny is asking for himself. Zoey would like Tucker to help her with Ben but he misunderstands. Riley accidentally sets up Bonnie with a lesbian client.

6.title: Never Ben Jealous
6.plot: Ben wants to prove that Danny is jealous of Riley's continued friendship with him, so he is willing to put himself in awkward situations involving Riley to get Danny jealous. Tucker continues to have casual sexual flings with Sondra, but ends up finally calling things off for good, having reached his patience with her annoying high-pitched voice. Riley is tasked with giving a heartfelt speech to Bernard Bender, one of the elderly founding members of her law firm who is retiring. Bonnie plans to use the opportunity to get close to Mr. Bender to elevate her real estate ...

7.title: The Return of the Mommy
7.plot: Emma's mother returns and wants to see Emma, but Ben is hesitant and Tucker lives in fear since he thinks Mary Hart is out to get him, and Bonnie is temporarily managing the bar and takes the opportunity to try out some new ideas.

8.title: Room-Mating
8.plot: When Sam considers quitting her job at the bar because of a long commute Ben has the perfect solution. But mostly perfect for Ben. Bonnie starts a new job and hires Tucker as her assistant but things go terribly wrong.

9.title: Stupid Cupid
9.plot: Riley pulls some tricks to get Ben and Zoey together. Tucker tries to get a new job in the television business but Bonnie gets in his way. Danny wants to be a sports commentator.

10.title: Homecoming and Going
10.plot: After Ben and Zoey innocently spend the night together Sam shows an interest in Ben. She invites him, Riley, and Danny to the beach where a secret is revealed. Bonnie mishears a Skype message and thinks Brad is leaving her.

11.title: Trial by Liar
11.plot: Riley is still heartbroken about finding out that Danny and Sam slept with each other back in high school and in puts Danny in a mock trial over her broken heart. Ben blackmails Zoey into pretending to date him.

12.title: Ben-semination
12.plot: Ben discovers Tucker has been making extra cash by visiting a sperm bank. To help Tucker pick up a nurse at the bank, Ben agrees to donate his own sperm but quickly regrets his decision after a couple chooses his sample. Meanwhile, Riley and Danny fight while attempting to host their friend's engagement party.

13.title: High School Diplomacy
13.plot: Ben confesses he didn't graduate from high school and it seems Bonnie didn't either. They need to take a make up test where Bonnie cheats and Ben is attracted to the teacher. Riley and Sam bond over getting into their school's hall of fame.

14.title: Not So Great Grandma
14.plot: When Ben invites Bonnie's estranged mother to family day at Emma's school, tensions run high and old wounds are opened. Riley and Tucker take an improv class.

15.title: Unholy Matrimony
15.plot: Ben pretends to be his mom's husband Brad when Bonnie's co-workers doubt his existence. Danny turns a fake relationship into reality with star Elena to make Riley jealous when she starts dating Ross again.

16.title: Double Date Double Down
16.plot: Ben and Riley realize they are in for more than they bargained for with dating older, more mature adults, and work to come up with a plan to get out of their respective relationships. When Bonnie and Tucker gain insider information about players on Danny's hockey team, they bet against the Rangers to win some cash.

17.title: The Love Seat
17.plot: Ben receives an anonymous note from a past love interest asking for a second chance, and does whatever he can to find the mystery girl. Danny misunderstands a note he thought was left for him and tries to get Riley back. Meanwhile, Tucker, Riley, and Bonnie enter Emma into a baby beauty pageant to get footage for Tucker's news segment.

18.title: She Said, Ben Said
18.plot: Ben and Sam are finally a couple, and decide to have their first date. However, misunderstandings on what they want on the date, lead to Danny and Riley getting involved in their relationship, making matters worse. Tucker is dating his dad's secretary Rene (Chelsea Harris). After getting suspicious assumptions from Bonnie, Tucker begins to believe that his dad is also dating Rene.

19.title: Condom Conundrum
19.plot: Emma pokes holes in Ben's condoms using Bonnie's lost earring. Danny and Tucker have also been using Ben's condoms causing a pregnancy scare among the guys fearing that their respective significant others Riley, Rene and Sam are pregnant. Riley has difficulty dealing with an incompetent new assistant and asks for Bonnie's advice on firing him.

20.title: My Fair Emma
20.plot: Ben tries to make things right with Emma; Danny and Riley are offered new career opportunities; Brad returns home; Tucker has exciting news but no one to share with.

locations: CBS Studio Center - 4024 Radford Avenue, Studio City, Los Angeles, California, USA
imdb.plot outline: Ben becomes a surprise dad to a baby girl when she's left on his doorstep by an ex-girlfriend. Ben decides to raise the baby with the help of his mother, his brother Danny, his friend Tucker and Riley the girl who is harboring a secret crush on him.
imdb.title: Baby Daddy
plot: A 20-something bachelor bartender becomes an unlikely parent when an ex-girlfriend leaves a baby girl on his doorstep.::Anonymous

Ben becomes a surprise dad to a baby girl when she's left on his doorstep by an ex-girlfriend. Ben decides to raise the baby with the help of his mother, his brother Danny, his friend Tucker and Riley the girl who is harboring a secret crush on him.::ABC Family

Ben, a bartender and lady's man, becomes an unexpected parent when one of his old girlfriends leaves a baby girl on his doorstep. With some help from his mom and roommates he might just learn what it means to be a parent, but not before he gets himself into some trouble.

A year after hooking up with a girl, Ben Wheeler, finds out he's a dad. The baby is dropped off at his doorstep and Ben must now seek help from his brother Danny, his mom Bonnie, his best friend Tucker and his childhood friend Riley. Baby Emma helps Ben become a mature young man and father. Meanwhile feelings are being developed and some have long been there and a love triangle is created, who ends up with who?
